						               													<description>UNITY is a board game for 2 to 3 players, in which each player strives to unite his pieces&amp;hellip; at any cost. By sacrificing the right pieces at crucial moments, you can shatter your opponents' groups as they coalesce, or eliminate a pesky splinter group of your own pieces &amp;mdash; anything to create unity.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In UNITY, each player&amp;rsquo;s pieces start dispersed on the board. Your goal is to create a single group of connected pieces of your colour of any size (even just one piece).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;UNITY was initially designed for 2 players, with the neutral pieces being just unmovable discs, but was later adapted to accommodate a 3rd player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Basic and Deluxe editions have been replaced by the new Unified Edition, that contains:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; A board with 91 hexagonal spaces.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; A supply of rectangular walls.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; 15 ring-shaped pieces of each colour (purple, orange, and green).&amp;#10;&amp;bull; 15 asterisk-shaped pieces of each colour.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; One counter of each colour to show which player is which colour.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; A carrying case&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
